Oct 26 2009 	Great hotel at a very good value!	My Grandmother and I stayed at this hotel from October 4th to October 11, 2009. First of all, the service of this hotel is excellent, more like a 5 star hotel. There was a wide range of travelers from Business to senior groups to families with kids. The staffs all around the hotel were very professional yet friendly and approachable to every guest. Grace at the front desk always has a nice smile and Micheal at room service is always energetic with a can-do attitude. I think they were extra attentive to us since my grandmother is 78 and has problem walking. Also due to that problem, we stayed in our hotel room quite often using room service and when we did go out (only about 5 hours each day), we just went to one attraction per day by taxi. Since the hotel has a great location, taxi fare wasn't bad at all. It was only a 15 minutes ride to the airport, 25 to 30 minutes to most attractions. The farthest we went was the Mall of the Emirates which took about 45 minutes by taxi.The room itself is spacious and clean, and it really does look like the pictures on the website. It is very new and modern, more like a 5 star hotel room. We really enjoyed our comfortable beds and pillows (much better than many other big hotel chains). Although we only booked the Classic room, the sitting area was still pretty spacious and comfortable, so we ordered room service quite often (as my grandmother can't go out much). To be honest, the food at this hotel wasn't very good for its price. There are so many restaurants in Dubai (from local small Arabian restaurants to fine dining at other 5 star hotels), where you can get much better food for the same price or less.All in all, it was a great hotel at a very good value. Since this hotel was only a mid-range hotel in Dubai, we didn't know what to expect. But after staying there, I must say that it was actually even better than many other hotels I've been in the upper-range categories.A few tips for saving a few bucks!- there is a local supermarket just outside of the hotel, so you can stock up on drinks and snacks instead of using the drinks inside your hotel room fridge. When you walk outside of the hotel, turn right, and then turn right again into the first street, walk straight for about 20 meters, you'll see a sign of a small grocery store. You can't miss it.-use the hotel's free shuttle bus to Jumeirah Beach Park. It is pretty far from the hotel (about 45 minutes by taxi)-since there are 3 Four Points by Sheraton hotels in Dubai, make sure you tell the taxi driver that it's the one in Downtown Dubai on Mankhool road (around Majestic Hotel). Although most drivers would know which one after you say &quot;in downtown Dubai&quot;, 1 driver did not. So he drove us to another hotel, and then drove us to the right one, so we had to pay more taxi fare. I'm sure he didn't do this on purpose, but it's just good to make sure they know exactly which hotel it is at the very start.-use the free wireless internet in the lobby. You'll see many people in the lobby using their computers any time of the day. If you get it in your room, the daily rate is expensive.	
