Jul 17 2009 	I thoroughly recommend the Sheraton Downtown for excellent value	We stayed at the Four Points Sheraton Downtown for six nights in early July.We booked direct through the hotel’s website. When we arrived we were given a complimentary upgrade (coincidence?)The room was large, modern and very clean (see my pics), including large flat-screen tv, safe, etc., and had a very comfortable king-size bed. Our upgraded room had a low table, settee and armchair, and a separate table and chairs. There is a very nice pool on the roof which was always kept very clean and is great to work on the tan or just to laze around. There were only about two dozen loungers when we were there which was adequate; it may not be so during the busier months. There is also a gym (apparently). There is a free bus to the public beach several times each day except Mondays (ladies’ day). I recommend at least one visit to the beautifully kept public beach. Staff throughout the hotel were excellent - always very friendly and welcoming. Particular praise should go to the guy who cleaned our room spotlessly every day. In my opinion, having tried both options, you’re either in a beach hotel in Dubai or you’re not. If you are then you’ll be paying £160++ a night for the delightful privilege; we paid £32 a night at the Sheraton - the bargain of the year. A ten minute walk from the hotel will get you to the Bur Juman mall; a twenty minute walk is needed to get to the Creek (not recommended); otherwise you’ll be getting a taxi. This isn’t a problem as taxis are cheap and plentiful. A taxi to the airport is about £4, about the same to the new Dubai Mall or Festival City. (Always ask the driver for Four Points, Sheraton, Downtown, Mankhool Road when returning to the hotel, as there are four Sheraton properties in the city.)Don’t miss going to the Dubai Mall. It contains 1200 shops and absolutely no expense has been spared on its construction. Go to the lower ground floor and out to watch the fountains (It’s better than Bellagio’s in Vegas). For the best view cross over the bridge and stand in front of the Baker and Spice restaurant (or better still eat dinner there on their terrace – the best meal we had during our visit). While at the mall don’t miss seeing the aquarium – and the new Waitrose!If you can afford a beach hotel in Dubai then I recommend you always stay there. If not then I thoroughly recommend the Sheraton Downtown for excellent value. I would have no hesitation in staying there again.	
