bles, bang in the middle of the town - the complete meal for three including pints of squeezed juices was £15. Amazing value compared to the hotels.The Burj Al Arab is certainly worth a look, just bear in mind that the traffic moves pretty quick - it does test your reflexes, we also drove further down the coast to the Palm, the drive to the end is four miles straight out to sea!The Four Points by Sheraton hotel is ideally placed for touring around Dubai if you have a vehicle, being just on the south side of town.In conclusion we could not have wished for more from a city hotel.	
