Oct 14 2008 	Amazing little extras make me a raving fan	The Four Points Downtown is brand new and absolutely luxurious given the 500 AED price I got on the Sheraton website. A large clean room with a king-size bed, fluffy pillows, flat-panel TV, and lots of little goodies (including a scale!), and a free shuttle to the beach.What turned me into a total raving fan, however, was the service I got: 10 hours *after* I'd checked out I came back to the hotel, hot and dusty from a desert safari, just to pick up my luggage before my midnight flight. The bell captain asked, without prompting, if I'd like to freshen up. He then carried my bags up to their pool-spa, got me a towel, and showed me to the locker-rooms where I could shower and change. I was nonplussed by his graciousness and hospitality. And when I offered him a tip, he politely declined, saying that this was just typical Four Points service.I'm sold.	
Oct 12 2008 	Great Value for Money Hotel	I recently travelled to Dubai and stayed at this hotel for three nights. I arrived at the hotel at about 7am just wanting to leave my bag and get a bite to eat as check in is only 3pm. On arrival I was able to do all the check in paperwork etc and was advised that a room should be available by 11am. There is a small lounge area in the lobby with free wireless internet connection so decided to catch up on email etc. I was pleasantly surprised a couple of hours later that my room was available.I had booked a classic double room and it was huge in comparison to many European hotels. The room was spotless and the finishings were excellent. The room was on the 6th floor and very quiet, although I did hear an ocassional clang from the building site next door (only during the day). This was to be expected as Dubai is one giant construction site. I ordered room service twice and each time it was delivered within 20mins by very friendly waiters. Remember to put your do not disturb sign on your door if you are having a sleep-in, as housekeeping seems to go around relatively early. I was only unexpectedly disturbed once in the evening by somebody coming to check the mini-bar, but he was in and out within 5 minutes.Overall this is a great hotel. However if you would like a beach holiday or a romantic getaway there are better choices, although the hotel does offer a shuttle service to Jumeirah Beach Park. I was very happy with my stay at the hotel.I do have a couple of suggestions that some visitors may find useful. Traffic in Dubai is incredible so be prepared to get stuck in a traffic jam at least once. Although taxis are numerous and usually readily available I would suggest getting the telephone number of a reliable taxi company in order to book a taxi if necessary. I was caught out a couple of times in very long queues of people waiting for taxis and regretted not being able to call a taxi service. I would highly recommend the Big Bus Company hop on-hop off bus tours. You are able to purchase tickets from the hotel. The tickets are valid for 24 hours so try and do the longer tour in the afternoon and the shorter one the following morning. I was short of time so had to do both tours in one afternoon and wasn't able to hop-off as much as I would have liked. The ticket includes a dhow cruise as well as entry into Dubai Museum. If you decide to visit Atlantis on the Palm I would suggest going for the full day if possible and get entry into Dolphin Bay. A few friends and I only visited the aquarium (The Lost Chambers) and were slightly disappointed.	
Sep 28 2008 	5 star rooms and facilities 1 star reception	Booked for five nights due to early check in and stayed for 4. Having flown from Perth and landing at 5.45am we were a bit bewildered and very hot. We found a taxi easily and after a lengthy wait at receprion we were pleasantly surprised by outr room. The hotel was very modern and more like a 5 star. The breakfast menu in the 'family room' was reasonably priced. We didnt eat dinner there but the snack menus were great and very reasonably priced. We ate at a small restaurant around the corner called the Grand (next to a cracking little supermarket'. There 3 of us ate starters a curry each and drinks for about £12. There is also a burger king attached to the petrol station about 10 minutes walk away.  The swimming pool was great too with a view of the port. Concierge was great and very helpful but some of the reception staff were the most unhelpful ever. The Dhow Palace had more welcoming staff and a great barr with live music. Would stay at the sheraton downtown dubai again and it was definately situated in a better place than the sister hotel in Bur Dubai. The shuttle bus to the beach was also great and very reliable although the beach in August is not the best location in 45 degrees. Alos please avoid shopping at the Karama. Rip off / fake everything but it looks very good and they hassle you loads. The best shopping is the Burjaman which is 10 mins walk and about 2 mins in a taxi !Big Bus Tour is good, try and see Mall of the Emirates, Waafi, Gold Souk and a dhow cruise. Do one tour each day and pick up from Burjaman.	
