Aug 18 2008	Excellent value for money and location	This is my fourth time to Dubai and my ninth to the UAE. I chose this time not to stay at a beach hotel but in Bur Dubai instead. For the price, this is fantastic value - the hotel is spotlessly clean and the rooms are large with great amenities (large TV - better than mine at home!, sofa, dining/coffee tables, plenty of wardrobe space, tea and coffee making facilities etc). The rooftop pool is a good size with plenty of sun loungers and waiters on hand if you want to order food/drinks and have them by the pool.The breakfast is a buffet service and to say it has a wide range of food is an understatement! The hotel staff are very friendly and even let us have a late check-out at no extra charge.The hotel has a courtesy minibus which takes you to Jumeirah Beach and back again three times a day.A good point to make if you have a late departing flight - the hotel has changing rooms, lockers and showers next to the gym on the top floor, so you can freshen up even if you are not leaving the hotel until very late.Don't forget though, if you ARE staying here, you need to tell the taxi drivers &quot;The NEW Four Points Sheraton on Mankhool Road&quot; or they will take you to the older one nearby also in Bur Dubai! (one even tried to take us to the Sheraton in Deira!!)Don't get me wrong - if you want 5* luxury then stay on Jumeirah Beach (the Hilton Jumeirah is fab) but if you're looking for value for money with an excellently located hotel in downtown Dubai, then the Four Points Sheraton Downtown certainly delivers.	
